.TH MAILCMD 1
.SH NAME
mailcmd \- mail the output of a failed command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mailcmd
[
.B -m
.I addr
]...
.I command
.I line
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Mailcmd
runs the command line using
.IR rc (1).
If the command exits with an error status,
.I mailcmd
mails the command's output to the named addresses
(by default, the current user).
.PP
.I Mailcmd
is typically used to run automatic scripts such as those
started by
.IR cron (8).
.SH SOURCE
.B /rc/bin/mailcmd
.SH "SEE ALSO
.IR cron (8)
